Summary of modifications made in this fork
-------------------------------------------
This fork adapts Timeful for private, single-operator use. Notable changes
(some in progress) include:

  * Removed: Stripe/billing, Discord & Slack bots, friends, availability
    groups, contacts/directory features, third-party analytics
    (PostHog/GTM), and the email/Listmonk reminder system.
  * Event creation, editing, and summaries are restricted to the operator and
    served only over a private Tailscale network; the public site at
    meet.jackdehaan.com is response-only.
  * Backend runs as Go + MongoDB in Docker, exposed publicly via Cloudflare
    Tunnel (poll/respond API only), with a static frontend on Vercel.
  * Google Calendar integration is operator-only.
  * Re-themed to a dark visual style.

Individual modified source files carry a notice indicating that they were
changed and the date of change, per AGPL-3.0 section 5(a).

